            <seg xml:id="C07g_app388-fThomas_start"/>stump. <seg xml:id="C07g_app388-fThomas_end"/>When we visited it the next <seg xml:id="C07g_app391-fThomas_start"/>morning, <seg xml:id="C07g_app391-fThomas_end"/>we found the <seg xml:id="C07g_app394-fThomas_start"/>tree shattered in a <seg xml:id="C07g_app394-fThomas_end"/>singular manner. It was not splintered by the shock, but entirely reduced to thin <seg xml:id="C07g_app397-fThomas_start"/>ribbands <seg xml:id="C07g_app397-fThomas_end"/>of wood. <seg xml:id="C07g_app399-fThomas_start"/>I never <seg xml:id="C07g_app399-fThomas_end"/>
